In reference to providing equal access to people with disabilities,
blind people specifically:

I've recently seen braille on some ATM machines in my area.  My
question is, how is the person supposed to know the functions of the
screen keys as the screens change at each step of the process of using
the machine.  Do banks provide a braille handbook with the sequence of
screens for certain transactions?

